The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Feb. 19: The PFRDA board has cleared the appointment of six fund managers for managing pension funds of non-government employees. Besides, approval to six fund managers, the board also cleared 23 entities for operating as points of presence and broadly agreed with the investment norms recommended by the expert group, PFRDA chairman D. Swarup said.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 19: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority (IRDA) will come out with merger and acquisition norms by the end of next month that would facilitate consolidations in the sector. The guidelines for merger and acquisition would be ready by March end, IRDA member actuary R. Kannan said.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 19: The department of telecom will do a special audit of Reliance Communications telecom licence companies, Jyotiraditya Scindia, minister of state for telecom and IT, said.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 19: The government is considering bringing in legislation to forfeit the Rs 8,804 crore in frozen demat accounts, stand-in finance minister Pranab Mukherjee said.                             
	 Mumbai, Feb. 19: The employee union of the RBI will go on a one-day strike to press their demands on pension tomorrow, affecting normal operations.                                                                                                                           
